The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Pak tribunal to meet Tuesday

Lahore: A commission formed by the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) to hear the appeals of fast bowlers Shoaib Akhtar and Mohammad Asif against their doping bans will meet on Tuesday, a PCB official said on Saturday. 

The members have informed us they are ready to hold their meeting on the 14th, the official said. He hoped there would be a verdict within a week. 

Hair was second best 

Darrell Hair was officially rated the worlds second-best umpire by the ICC before it sacked him. In its last annual personal appraisal, prepared by ICCs umpiring bosses, Hair was ranked equal-second on the Elite Panel with outstanding Simon Taufel believed to be No. 1, a report in an Australian daily said. (Reuters) 




